Karl Hammar
owl:Ontology.dc:description: This ontology imports all RealEstateCore (REC) modules and thus gives the fullest expressivity that REC allows. You can use this ontology as-is, or you can construct your own ontology by importing individual REC modules.
owl:Ontology.dc:title: RealEstateCore Full
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment:
Version 3.0 is a major and compatibility-breaking refactoring of REC:
* Properties have been defined as being (at-most) single-domain and single-range, supporting usability and visualization. * Meronomy properties have been refactored to allow transitive traversal of the parthood hierarchy from RealEstate all the way down to individual devices using the isPartOf and hasPart superproperties. ** This has required refactoring of the relations Building <-> BuildingComponent and Device <-> DeviceComponent (the latter is removed). * Class naming has been simplified (BuildingStructure -> Building, BuildingStructureComponent -> BuildingComponent, etc). * A (minimal) representation of GeoSPARQL has been integrated, to allow for standardized geospatial representations and querying. REC home-made geospatial/location vocabulary is phased out as a consequence. * Alignments against other ontologies or standards (BIP, Belok, IPSO, Haystack, fi2xml, IFC) have been broken out into separate alignment files * Module boundaries have been clarified and three new modules (Lease, Metadata, Agents) have been added, in preparation of anticipated modelling work. * All entities have been assigned rdfs:labels and the large majority rdfs:comments. * The modules have been documented with metadata using DC, CC, VANN, cpannotationschema, etc. * All IRI:s are now HTTPS

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Where appropriate, named places or time periods can be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Coverage

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as the W3CDTF profile of ISO 8601.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Date

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Examples of dimensions include size and duration. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the list of Internet Media Types.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Format

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Identifier

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC 4646.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Language

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Relation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Rights

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Source

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. To describe the spatial or temporal topic of the resource, use the Coverage element.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Subject

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the Format element.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Type

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as the W3CDTF profile of ISO 8601 [W3CDTF].
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Date

The default geometry to be used in spatial calculations. It is Usually the most detailed geometry.
GeoSPARQL is Copyright (c) 2012 Open Geospatial Consortium, Inc. All Rights Reserved. http://www.opengeospatial.org/ogc/document.

A spatial representation for a given feature.
GeoSPARQL is Copyright (c) 2012 Open Geospatial Consortium, Inc. All Rights Reserved. http://www.opengeospatial.org/ogc/document.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasGeometry

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An online account that an Agent holds.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: account

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the member Agents that are part of a certain Group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has member

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that links a Person to an image that represents them.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: image

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an Organization to an image/logo that represents them. This is stricter than FOAF, in which logo has domain "Thing"; but it works for our domain.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: logo

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a Device of some sort to an Event generated by, detected through, or targetting that Device.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: associated with event

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking BuildingComponents to Devices mounted within them.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contains mounted device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The measurement unit used by some Device.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: device measurement unit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Quantity Kind that a device measures or affects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: device quantity kind

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A unit used to measure some aspect of some Event.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: event measurement unit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Quantity Kind that an event measures or affects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: event quantity kind

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking Buildings to the Building Components that they are made up of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has building component

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Associates a building with a point in some coordinate reference system which can be used to resolve local (building-specific) coordinates against this outer coordinate reference system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has geo-reference origo

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The unit that something (sensor observations, device capabilities, physical measurements, etc) is measured by. This is given as an object property with a corresponding class (rather than a simple datatype property) since one unit may have many serialized representations and may be used for many different types of measurements.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has measurement unit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse properties of the isPartOf property tree, used for top-down traversal of the parthood hierarchy.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has part

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links entities that are measurable to the Quantity Kind that they measure, e.g., Temperature, Pressure, etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has quantity kind

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking a piece of RealEstate to its constituent components (i.e., Buildings and Land).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has real estate component

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking BuildingComponents to their constituent sub-components.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has sub-BuildingComponent

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking a Device to any sub-Devices that it contains.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has sub-device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property to model nesting of building components, e.g., rooms within apartments or walls within stairwells, etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has super-BuildingComponent

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A property that allows for nesting of devices within devices.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has super-Device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property describing in which Building Component (most typically a Room) that a Device is mounted.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is mounted in Building Component

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A generic clustering of meronomy (parthood) relations, allowing for the traversal of the parthood taxonomy of a real estate. Note that this is a transitive property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates which Building a certain Building Component is part of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of building

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a Building or a piece of Land belongs to / is part of a given Real Estate.
A unit used to specificy some Quantity Kind, such as temperature, pressure, etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: quantity kind measurement unit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The coverage or impact area of a given device or sensor. For example: an air-treatment Device might serve several Rooms or a full Building. Note that devices can also service one another, e.g., an air-treatment Device might serve an air diffuser Device.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serves

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates how a Device serves an entire Building.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serves building

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates how a Device serves a particular Building Component (e.g., a Room).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serves building component

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates how a Device serves another Device.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: serves device

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Groups the subset of device configuration settings that are expressed using named individuals (for configuration attributes that are modelled with datatype properties, see datatype hasCommunicationAttribute).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has communication configuration

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: has communications bus

Property that models Premises (leasable parts of real estate) parthood, i.e., that certain buildings and/or rooms are part of a defined Premise (which can in turn by governed by a Lease through a LeaseContract)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of premises

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Leasable object (e.g., property, equipment, etc) that this a lease of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: lease of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The agent (organization or person) leasing some leasable object, i.e., the user of the asset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: leasee

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The agent (organization or person) leasing out some leasable object, i.e., the owner of the asset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: leasor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parthood traversal property linking Premises to their constituent Buildings or Rooms.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: premises includes

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A lease is regulated by some contract entered into by the leasor and leasees.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: regulated by

Connects a geometry object with its text-based serialization.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has serialization

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person's family name.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: family name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person's first name (if they have one; this varies across cultural contexts).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: first name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A gender designation for a Person. Stricter than FOAF, which allows all Agents to have gender.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gender

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person's personal, individual name.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: given name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person's last name (if they have one; this varies across cultural contexts).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: last name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A name for some Agent. Stricter than FOAF, we assume that things that have names are Agents, not Things (e.g., other predicates will need be used to described identifiers for non-Agents).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to map an Id in an external system to an instance (e.g. an UUID).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has alias ID

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This parent property groups a number of sub-properties that provide additional richness to building or device model and that are often used in practice in various systems, but which have not yet (REC 3.0) been fully modelled their respecive REC modules.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has auxiliary data

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a city that a certain Geometry is part of.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has city

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Extra information about an object that is of a more exceptional character. E.g. "This Device needs to be replaced no later than 2020", "Note: Black color is used to mark warmwater inlet"
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has comment

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a country that a certain Geometry is part of.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has country

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Measured in ms (milliseconds). Duration is defined as the length of time that something lasts.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has duration

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
The angle between one of the axis of a local coordinate system within e.g. a building and a north-south meridian. The angle is measured between the meridian and the local coordinate axis and counted as positive to the east side of the meridan (neagtive to the west side).
Bearings are never greater than 90Â°. Bearings are based on true north.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has geo reference bearing

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
Linking to https://www.geonames.org
E.g. for Stockholm (Sweden): LocationUUID#1 hasGenonames http://www.geonames.org/2673730/stockholm.html
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has geonames ID

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Designation or enumeration commenly found on blueprints for an object. E.g. text designating a Device or a Room.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has littera

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This property is a cognitive clustering for human consumption, grouping sub-properties that assign labels (e.g., place names, addresses, etc.) to Geometry entities. This branch of the property hierarchy may need some further development and cleaning up in future versions.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has location attribute

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Human-readable-friendly name.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has popular name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Address used for postal delivery.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has postal address

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a region that a certain Geometry is part of.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has region

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Used for information about a source system or data.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has source

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates any sustainability certifications that a Building or piece of Real Estate has achieved. This is a stub for now and will likely be more expressively modelled as classes and properties in future REC releases.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has sustainability certification

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment:
Cognitive clustering of time-related properties that can apply to time-indexed objects (i.e., events of various sorts).
Certain time properties are given using xsd:DateTime, i.e., ISO8601 (see below), whereas others are given as ints or floats, depending on use case.
Time format ISO8601:
Complete date, hour, minutes, seconds, and decimal fraction of second
YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD (eg 1997-07-16T19:20:30.45+01:00)
Where: YYYY = 4 numbers for year. MM = 2 numbers for month (01=January, etc.) DD = 2 numbers for day of month (01 till 31) hh = 2 numbers for hour (00 till 23) (am/pm not allowed) mm = 2 numbers for minutes (00 till 59) ss = 2 numbers for second (00 till 59) s = 1 or more numbers represent a decimal fraction of second
TZD = time zone designator (Z or +hh:mm or -hh:mm) Time is expressed in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time), with designated UTC ("Z") for GMT.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An event may be associated with a value. This is a rather generic property which can be reused or extended by sub-classes to indicate, e.g., measurement values, actuation values, etc.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has value

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An address for visiting the Geometry. If a Geometry has multiple visiting addresses, then just add as many hasVistingAddress as needed.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has visting address

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a certain Geometry's zip code.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has zip code

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Expressed as a string adhering to the notation "(x,y,z)", where x, y, and z ar whole or decimal numbers indicating the position in the local building coordinate system, measured in meters. This relates to the outside world coordinate refence system via the values expressed by GeoReferenceOrigo.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: is located at local coordinates

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The syntactical representation of a unit, e.g., m^3 for cubic meter, etc.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: unit sign

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The payload of a command sent by the building management system to the underlying actuator(s).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuation command

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The payload of an incoming request to a building management system that it should perform an actuation; to be sent onward to a given Actuator.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuation request

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The value returned from an Actuator to the calling party.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: actuation response

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for the event of the underlying system intiating the actuation command.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has actuation command time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for when a request for an actuation arrived.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has actuation request time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time stamp for a possible response from actuation process.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has actuation response time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Groups the subset of device configuration attributes that are expressed using datatype properties (for configuration attributes that are modelled with named individuals, see object property hasCommunicationConfiguration).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has communication attribute

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Time when an object or result was processed in a system.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has processed time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Time at which a lease arrangement ends.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: lease end

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Time at which a lease arrangement begins.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: lease start

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
The class represents the top-level geometry type. This class is equivalent to the UML class GM_Object defined in ISO 19107, and it is superclass of all geometry types.
GeoSPARQL is Copyright (c) 2012 Open Geospatial Consortium, Inc. All Rights Reserved. http://www.opengeospatial.org/ogc/document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Geometry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A collection of individual Agents (included in the Group via the object property hasMember).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Group

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An organization of any sort (e.g., a business, association, project, consortium, tribe, etc.)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Organization

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A natural person (i.e., an individual human being).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A LaboratoryDry is a laboratory where computational or applied mathematical analyses are done on a computer-generated model to simulate a phenomenon in the physical realm.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LaboratoryDry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A LaboratoryWet is a type of laboratory where it is necessary to handle various types of chemicals and potential "wet" hazards, so the room has to be carefully designed, constructed, and controlled to avoid spillage and contamination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LaboratoryWet

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Room for making audio and/or video recordings. A.ka. studio.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RecordingRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Room for staff to take breaks.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: StaffRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The level of storey, a.k.a. floorplan
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Storey level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: For e.g. medical or other treatment or consultation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TreatmentRoom

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A non-physical Building. Belongs to a RealEstate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Virtual building

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A non-physical component. Belongs to a Building . One Building may have zero, one, or many Virtual components. E.g a temperature value from an external service for the area of a building.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Virtual building component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The human or machine that consumes or acts upon an object or data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A confined building structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Building

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The parts that makes up a building structure (Building). E.g., Room, Facade, RoofInner, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Building component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thing made or adapted for a particular purpose, specifically a piece of electronic equipment. A Device can contain subdevices or be part of superdevices. It is subclassed into more specific device types, e.g., Sensor, Actuator, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A spatiotemporally indexed entity with participants (e.g., something which occurs somewhere, and that has or takes some time). We do not on this top level define the particulars of how to model space or time; that is left to the implementing subclasses. Thus, in a sense, this is just a cognitive clustering for human consumers of the ontology, a root class from which all different types of events derive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Event

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A fixed point for e.g. a building structure. Commonly refered to as "insertion point" in CAD-programs. Used as origo for LocalCoordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Geo-reference origo

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A piece of land upon which one or more buildings may be situated.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Land

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
The measurment units that are used in RealEstateCore. Use SI-units in general. Store values without prefixes.
Exceptions to SI: Express temperature in Celsius, Energy in Watt hour (Wh), Angle i degrees (360 degress = 1 revolution) MillimeterPerHour for Precipation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Measurement unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes the type of values that can be observed by sensors or set by actuators. Inspired by QUDT.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quantity kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The legal/administrative representation of some lands and/or buildings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Real estate

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Types of objects that can make up a piece of real estate, e.g., land and buildings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Real estate component

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Base class for all more specific room types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Room

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The act of changing the state of something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A description of what kind of input the Actuator accepts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuation interface

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuator is a component that is responsible for moving and controlling a mechanism or system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BACnetConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instances of this class and its subclasses represent configuration fields and values in the various old-world non-IoT building system standards.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Communication configuration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Type of communications bus for the Device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Communications bus

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Events that are relevant in a Device context; initially observations, actuations, and exceptions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device events

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The main function or purpose of a Device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Device function type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Failed attempt or unexpected result when tried to do something (e.g. read a Sensor).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Exception

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: KNXConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LoRaConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MBusConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ModbusRTUConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ModbusTCPConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OPC-DAConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specific classes and properties to be extended in upcoming version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OPC-UAConfiguration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Observation of a phenomena. Made by a Sensor. Used with hasValue.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Observation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Description of the context or media that a sensor or actuator is operating within.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Placement context

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The power source for the device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Power source

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Thing which detects or measures a physical property and records, indicates, or otherwise responds to it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Things that can be leased (e.g., buildings, rooms, equipment, etc.).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Leasable

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Formal document that identifies the Tenant and the leased asset or property; states lease term and fee (rent), and detailed terms and conditions of the lease agreement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lease contract

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Premises are a set of buildings or rooms that are leased out to tenants, typically for a defined purpose.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Premises

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: When a human interacts with a system. E.g. pushes a button to turn on/off a light, force ventilation.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: AgentInteraction

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Temperature in Celsius degress. Note that correct SI Unit is Kelvin.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Celsius

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The angle between two electrical phases.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: CosPhi

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Volume is the quantity of three-dimensional space enclosed by a closed surface, for example, the space that a substance (solid, liquid, gas, or plasma) or shape occupies or contains. Volume is often quantified numerically using the cubic metre (m3).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: CubicMeter

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Total energy (not specified as Active or Reactive, used for e.g. district heating).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: EnergyTotal

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Light intensity in a specific area.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Lux
